The International Center for Policy and Conflict yesterday asked political parties and hopefuls to focus on issue-based campaigns.Executive director Wainaina Ndung u urged voters to elect leaders who give priority to security, economy, equality and job creation. We underscore the need to ensure the elections are conducted in peaceful, constructive and credible environment, Ndung u said.He said ICPC is ready to support the IEBC in taking steps to reinforce integrity in the electoral system. Information about these steps is not widely understood by many, he said.